


RECVCLR(2)          Xinu Programmer's Manual           RECVCLR(2)



NAME
     recvclr - clear incoming message buffer asynchronously

SYNOPSIS
     int recvclr()

DESCRIPTION
     A process executes _r_e_c_v_c_l_r to clear its message buffer of
     any waiting message in preparation for receiving messages.
     If a message is waiting, _r_e_c_v_c_l_r returns it to the caller.
     If no messages are waiting, _r_e_c_v_c_l_r returns OK.

SEE ALSO
     receive(2), send(2), preceive(2), psend(2)









































